# A Patch Personal Access Token (PAT) for the target instance. Mint it once in
# Patch -> Settings -> Tokens. The Manager exchanges it for a short-lived OWNER
# session (POST /functions/v1/pat-exchange) and talks to PostgREST as that owner —
# RLS-scoped, no service_role. Revoke it from the same Settings panel any time.
# It's a real credential: never commit it.
PATCH_PAT=pat_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# The deployment's public anon key is NOT secret and lives in the manifest
# ([backlog.patch].anon_key), not here.
#
# The Workers' `claude` CLI must be logged in on this host once (interactive claude
# inherits that auth — there is no per-Worker login). Nothing to set here for that.
